Ingredients Beans Onions Ripe plantains Cubes of your choice Palm oil Ground red tomatoes ground crayfish Ground red pepper to taste Salt to taste Procedure •Pick the beans to remove every unwanted material from the beans. Parboil the picked beans, cook for about 10 minutes then wash and set aside in a bowl. •Slice the fresh red tomatoes/pepper and onions and put in bowl. •Cook the beans  again until it is very soft for consumption. •Add the ground crayfish, cube, sliced tomatoes/peppers, palm oil, salt and pepper to taste. •Add water if the water has dried. Then  cook for some minutes •You can add fluted pumpkin if you like vegetables •Cook for another three minutes and it is ready. 